I" <p>rpm2cpio and yumdownloader</p>

<p>If you ever happen to want to get some files from an RPM to do whatever you want with them, you could:</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>yumdownloader &amp;lt;package&amp;gt; 
rpm2cpio &amp;lt;package.rpm&amp;gt; &amp;gt; file.cpio
cpio -idv &amp;lt; file.cpio # extracts from file.cpio all package files into the current working dir
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Pretty simple and small, but a good tool to have if you need it.</p>
:ET